# ci-watch watchlist -- which repos' CI to surface in the session dashboard.
#
# This .example is COMMITTED (the repo is public). Copy it to the REAL, gitignored
# file and put your actual repos there:
#
#   cp ~/.config/ci-watch/watchlist.example ~/.config/ci-watch/watchlist
#   $EDITOR ~/.config/ci-watch/watchlist
#
# NEVER put real owner/repo names in THIS .example file -- only in the gitignored
# watchlist (the `home/.ssh/config.local` privacy pattern).
#
# One target per line:
#   owner/repo@branch | optional label     watch a specific branch
#   owner/repo                             omit @branch -> latest run on any branch
# Lines starting with '#' are comments; blank lines are ignored.
#
# Examples (placeholders -- replace with your own):
#   your-org/your-service@main | my service
#   your-org/another-repo@develop
#
# A red target ESCALATES the longer it stays red and only clears when CI goes
# green or you deliberately snooze it:
#   ci-watch                          render now (what the session hook runs)
#   ci-watch --snooze <repo> <days>   deliberately silence a red (never "by seeing")
#   ci-watch --list
#   ci-watch --json
